South Africa’s largest cinema chain Ster-Kinekor has launched ‘Subscription Club’ – a service that will enable customers to watch unlimited movies at certain theatres for a monthly fee. Customers who subscribe to the Ster-Kinekor Fan Club will get four movies and 20% off popcorn and soda combo, for only R249 per month. For those who subscribe to the Ster-Kinekor MORvies Club, they get unlimited movies for only R349 per month, with 20% off popcorn and soda combo. The cinema chain pointed out that Ster-Kinekor Fan Club is only available at Watercrest, Ilanga and Eastgate, while MORvies Club will be available at Somerset, Garden Route Mall and Eastgate. Ster-Kinekor owns some 60-65% of the market, boasting some 55 movie complexes in South Africa (more than 400 screens and 64 000 seats) with 154 state-of-the-art 3D cinemas. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-317962" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Ster-Kinekor.png" alt="" width="1083" height="520" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Ster-Kinekor.png 1083w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Ster-Kinekor-300x144.png 300w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Ster-Kinekor-768x369.png 768w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Ster-Kinekor-1024x492.png 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 1362px) 62vw, 840px" /> Read: Movie ticket prices in South Africa: Ster-Kinekor vs Nu Metro